properties.abstract: An enjoyable after-work circuit or half-day tour with great panoramic views of the Landwasser valley and the mountains surrounding Davos. A particularly thrilling aspect of the route is the high-speed downhill run.
properties.description:
From the starting point at the sports centre (Sportzentrum) the route takes us along Talstrasse to Mattastrasse. From there it branches off into the Mattawald forest, where a gentle ascent to Clavadel awaits us. From Clavadel we continue up on a good trail to the Clavadeler Alp, with wonderful views of the mountains around Davos and the open Landwasser valley.

And for lovers of fresh Davos mountain cheese this vantage point is also the perfect spot. Indeed, besides its panoramic views the Clavadeler Alp also offers fresh cheese and other tasty treats. Now rested, we continue on our way with a slight ascent beyond the tree line to Usser Isch. After a leisurely and even section, the descent to Ischalp on the road is faster. 

A little below the middle station, the flow trail runs through the Bolgenwald forest towards Bolgen Plaza. Jetty curves and numerous flow passages will put a smile on your face during the final descent into the valley.
